land grabber
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a speculator who squatted on and/or purchased large tracts of land [often by spotting or gridironing].
Origin:[none]
Register: historical

Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
